## 🚨 Critical Issues (Must Fix Now)

### 1. The `is_done` Recursion Bug
```python
is_done = models.BooleanField(default=False)
@property
def is_done(self): return self.is_done  # <--- CRASH
```
*   **Pros of fixing**: Prevents the application from crashing.
*   **Cons**: None.
*   **Recommendation**: **🔴 MUST FIX IMMEDIATELY.** Delete the `@property` block.

### 2. Lesson Completion is Incorrectly Global
```python
done = self.lessons.filter(is_done=True).count()
```
*   **Pros of fixing**: Makes your site actually work for more than 1 user.
*   **Cons**: Requires updating the [completion_percentage](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#47-53) and [is_finished](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#54-67) methods.
*   **Recommendation**: **🔴 MUST FIX IMMEDIATELY.** We already planned this with the [UserLessonProgress](file:///c:/Users/francis/OneDrive/Desktop/DJANGO%20PROJECT/e-learning/courses/models.py#88-97) model. I need your permission to update `Module.py` to fix this.

